# Blog Routing & Code

## URL structure

All blog posts live at `/blog/[category]/[subcategory]/[slug]`.

```
✅ /blog/industry/lawyers/puede-la-ia-sustituir-al-notario
❌ /blog/puede-la-ia-sustituir-al-notario
```

## Always use `getPostUrl()` — never hardcode the path

```ts
// ✅ GOOD
import { getPostUrl } from "@/lib/blog";
<Link href={getPostUrl(post)} />

// ❌ BAD
<Link href={`/blog/${post.slug}`} />
```

This applies in: `PostCard`, `RelatedPosts`, prev/next navigation, RSS route, schema.org JSON-LD, canonical meta tags, and `ShareButtons`.

## ShareButtons takes a full URL, not a slug

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<ShareButtons title={post.title} url={canonical} />  // canonical = SITE_URL + getPostUrl(post)

// ❌ BAD
<ShareButtons title={post.title} slug={post.slug} />
```

## Route file layout

```
src/app/blog/
  page.tsx                              # /blog listing
  layout.tsx
  rss.xml/route.ts
  [category]/
    [subcategory]/
      [slug]/page.tsx                   # canonical post page
```

Do NOT add a `[category]/page.tsx` alongside `[category]/[subcategory]/[slug]/page.tsx` —
Next.js throws "different slug names for the same dynamic path".
Legacy slug redirects belong in `next.config.ts`, not as a route file.
